  "observation": "Brainstorm triggered by plateau. 4 proposals generated.",
  "suggestion": "The plateau is not due to local optima within the current search space — it is due to search space saturation. All agents have converged to similar locally-optimal solutions because the fitness landscape is static, unimodal, and homogeneous. The system needs *changing* selection pressure, not better optimization. Environmental dynamism (Proposal 1), morphological degrees of freedom (Proposal 2), or adversarial coevolution (Proposal 3) all introduce *new axes* of optimization that cannot be solved by refining existing strategies. The agent population has found the peak of a fixed hill; what's needed is a moving target, a bigger hill, or a competing hill.; [medium] Introduce dynamic environmental cycles with temporal beauty rewards. Add seasonal resource availability (oscillating nutrient distribution), periodic predators (ghost agents that hunt for N cycles then disappear), and beauty scoring that rewards motion patterns synchronized to environmental phase. Organisms locked in static morphology can't adapt to changing threats and opportunities. — Plateau exists because the fitness landscape is static — organisms converge to fixed solutions. Dynamic environment forces continuous re-adaptation. Temporal beauty (rewarding 'dance-like' or 'breathing' movement patterns that sync with world cycles) cannot be solved by static morphology. Creates open-ended pressure.; [hard] Introduce cell differentiation during growth. Allow cells to specialize into types (sensory, motor, storage, reproductive, structural) with different energetic costs and behavioral rules. Cells choose their type based on local signals during growth. This expands morphospace exponentially — same cell count can now express vastly more phenotypes. — Current agents are homogeneous cell networks. Specialization unlocks new strategies: organisms can build brains (sensory+motor clusters) separate from stomachs (storage), enable true multi-organ coordination. Fitness plateau suggests search space is exhausted; specialization multiplies available solutions by orders of magnitude.; [medium] Introduce explicit coevolutionary predator species. Create a second species type that consumes primary agents; predator fitness = organisms eaten. Prey fitness becomes relative (survival in presence of predators), not absolute. Remove static beauty from predator fitness — they evolve purely for predation efficiency. This forces arms race dynamics. — Beauty-optimization has converged. Predators break convergence by shifting the goal posts — prey organisms can't achieve perfect fitness because their predators adapt to counter them. This creates cyclic arms-race dynamics that prevent stagnation. Adds new selection pressure orthogonal to current objectives.",
